(Design Module Unauthorized Issue - Explanation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Problem) Tj
T*
(1. The UI login was working and users could open pages.) Tj
T*
(2. But several protected backend actions returned 401 Unauthorized.) Tj
T*
(3. The main failure was on POST /api/leads/:id/complete-task.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Root Cause) Tj
T*
(1. The backend protects many routes by calling getUserFromSession\(req\).) Tj
T*
(2. That means those requests must include Authorization: Bearer <sessionId>.) Tj
T*
(3. In the lead detail page, some protected fetch calls were still sending no session header.) Tj
T*
(4. When those requests reached the backend without the token, the session lookup failed and backend returned 401.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this happened even after login) Tj
T*
(1. Logging in only proves the browser has a sessionId stored.) Tj
T*
(2. Each protected API call still has to send that sessionId in the Authorization header.) Tj
T*
(3. So page load could work while a specific action still failed as Unauthorized.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Secure Solution Applied \(Option 1\)) Tj
T*
(1. We kept backend protection in place.) Tj
T*
(2. We added a shared helper: buildAuthHeaders\(sessionId, headers\).) Tj
T*
(3. We updated protected lead-detail requests to always send Authorization: Bearer <sessionId>.) Tj
T*
(4. This was applied to the protected lead fetches and complete-task flow in the lead page.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this is secure) Tj
T*
(1. Backend still validates the acting user for protected routes.) Tj
T*
(2. Task completion and other actions are tied to the real logged-in user.) Tj
T*
(3. This protects auditability and supports future Google Calendar event ownership safely.) Tj
T*
(4. We did not weaken backend security by removing auth checks.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Files changed for this fix) Tj
T*
(1. my-app/app/lib/apiBase.ts) Tj
T*
(2. my-app/app/Leads/[id]/page.tsx) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Result) Tj
T*
(Protected lead-detail requests now use the stored session token consistently.) Tj
T*
(This is the correct long-term pattern for the module.) Tj
ET
